                    </div>
                    <span>It is the best sports book I have ever read! The author pulled no punches in detailing the amazing story of Braddock. The boxer's highs and lows were vividly portrayed. You could smell the gym, feel the training, and taste the victory. Moreover, the political, economic and social state of the world in those times was marvelously woven into the fabric of the story. This book was truly a joy to experience. By the end of the story, two champions emerged, Braddock and Schaap.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">This has been a great read!!!</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
